<paragraph id="8BDB1745FFFEFFF7FF111972FD75DA5B" blockId="23.[151,1436,1158,1689]" box="[199,648,1374,1401]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FF111972FE83DA5B" bold="true" box="[199,382,1374,1401]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Common name</emphasis>
. Wandering pond snail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E44CEFFFEFFF7FF1119AFFED9DAC7" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDB1745FFFEFFF7FF1119AFFED9DAC7" blockId="23.[151,1436,1158,1689]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FF1119AFFEA6DABF" bold="true" box="[199,347,1411,1437]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Morphology</emphasis>
. Medium-sized snail (shell up to 
<quantity id="4C9CBAA0FFFEFFF7FD0519AFFCDFDABF" box="[723,802,1411,1437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
high). Shell is thin, light, horny and translucent. A weak lip can be found inside the aperture, on occasions. For more details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF56AB4FFFEFFF7FC64198BFB25DAE3" author="Welter-Schultes, F. W." box="[946,1240,1446,1473]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref60074" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification, planet poster editions. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 674 pp. [in German]" type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes (2012: 53</bibRefCitation>
, figure on the top of the page).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E44CEFFFEFFF7FF1119C2FDDAD826" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDB1745FFFEFFF7FF1119C2FAB9D973" blockId="23.[151,1436,1158,1689]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FF1119C2FE0FD92B" bold="true" box="[199,498,1518,1545]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. Palearctic species preferring stagnant and slow-flowing waters, rich with vegetation, and muddy, gravel or rocky substrate (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF56AB4FFFEFFF7FDA91A3FFC8BD90F" author="Welter-Schultes, F. W." box="[639,886,1555,1581]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref60074" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification, planet poster editions. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 674 pp. [in German]" type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF56AB4FFFEFFF7FC571A3FFBF8D90F" author="Gloer, P." box="[897,1029,1555,1581]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref47000" refString="Gloer, P. (2019) The freshwater gastropods of the West-Palaearctis. Biodiversity Research Laboratory, Hetlingen, 399 pp." type="book" year="2019">Glöer 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F37357D5FFFEFFF7FBE01A3FFB7DD90F" box="[1078,1152,1555,1581]" name="Serbia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, it was found in the Dan- ube, Sava, Tisza, Begej, Zapadna Morava and Nišava Rivers, DTD canal system, and in Zasavica Wetland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB1745FFFEFFF7FF111A76FC9FD9BB" blockId="23.[151,1436,1158,1689]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FF111A76FE87D957" bold="true" box="[199,378,1626,1653]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Other remarks</emphasis>
. Shell morphology very variable (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF56AB4FFFEFFF7FD2F1A77FC22D957" author="Schniebs, K. &amp; Gloer, P. &amp; Vinarski, M. V. &amp; Hundsdoerfer, A. K." box="[761,991,1627,1653]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="657 - 678" refId="ref54999" refString="Schniebs, K., Gloer, P., Vinarski, M. V. &amp; Hundsdoerfer, A. K. (2011) Intraspecific morphological and genetic variability in Radix balthica (Linnaeus 1758) (Gastropoda: Basommatophora: Lymnaeidae) with morphological comparison to other European Radix species. Journal of Conchology, 40 (6), 657 - 678." type="journal article" year="2011">
Schniebs 
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FCB11A77FC62D957" box="[871,927,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF56AB4FFFEFFF7FC3D1A77FB92D957" author="Gloer, P." box="[1003,1135,1627,1653]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref47000" refString="Gloer, P. (2019) The freshwater gastropods of the West-Palaearctis. Biodiversity Research Laboratory, Hetlingen, 399 pp." type="book" year="2019">Glöer 2019</bibRefCitation>
). On the IUCN Red List of threatened species, it has been assessed as LC (Vavrova 2011 
<emphasis id="B910CB57FFFEFFF7FC921A53FCAFD9BB" box="[836,850,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">b</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB1745FFFEFFF7FF411AC6FDDAD826" blockId="23.[151,551,1770,1797]" box="[151,551,1770,1797]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
